<number box="[392,452,1738,1762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" value="1900.0">1900</number>
a: 
<number box="[479,525,1737,1762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" value="153.0">153</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In order to fix the identity of the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1090,1737,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Anthomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis box="[1009,1090,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">fulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I have labelled and designate herewith this ♂ as 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[361,468,1773,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<typeStatus box="[361,468,1773,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">lectotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. It is a valid species of 
<taxonomicName box="[732,836,1774,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,836,1774,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Pegomya</emphasis>
